section.def:
dose
                (劑量) is the quantity of absorbed energy from
            radiation;

dose rate (劑量率) is the
            dose per unit of time, usually expressed as grays per minute and symbolized Gy/min. or
            as sieverts per minute and symbolized Sv/min.;

dosemeter
                (劑量計) means an instrument for measuring exposure
            to radiation;

licence
                (牌照) means a licence issued under section
                9 of the Ordinance;

paragraph.content:
in the case of a person employed in radiation work, the dose limit;
                        or (L.N. 225 of 1990; L.N. 154 of
                            1995)

subsection.def:
registered Chinese medicine
                    practitioner (註冊中醫) has the meaning
                given by section 2(1) of the Chinese Medicine Ordinance (Cap. 549);

paragraph.content:
1.5 mm thickness of aluminium for an apparatus with a maximum voltage not
                    exceeding 70
                    kV;

2.5 mm thickness of aluminium for an apparatus with a maximum voltage
                    exceeding 70
                    kV;
